{"word":"Ὀρχομενός","slug":"Ὀρχομενός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n75502\" key=\"*)orxomeno/s\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Ὀρχομενός</orth>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ὁ</gen>, also <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ἡ</gen> (<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0003.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:113\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Th.\">Th.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.113</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0001.tlg001.perseus-grc1:4:257\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ A.R.\">A.R.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.257</biblScope> </bibl>), the name of several Greek cities, the most famous of which was <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Ὀρχομενὸς Μινύειος</foreign> in Boeotia, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:2:511\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.511</biblScope></bibl>, etc.:—<pos opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pos\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Adj.\">Adj.</a></pos> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Ὀρχομένιος</orth>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0627.tlg028.perseus-grc1:7\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hp.\">Hp.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ulc.\">Ulc.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">7</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0016.tlg001.perseus-grc1:9:16\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hdt.\">Hdt.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">9.16</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ SIG\">SIG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">519.7</biblScope> </bibl> (Aegium, <date TEIform=\"date\">iii B. C.</date>), <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0099.tlg001.perseus-grc1:9:2:40\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Str.\">Str.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">9.2.40</biblScope> </bibl> :—hence <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Ὀρχομενίζω</orth>, <sense id=\"n75502.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">side with the Orchomenians,</tr_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0539.tlg001:81\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hellanic.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">81</biblScope> </bibl> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ J.\">J.</a></author> </bibl> (but perh. not <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hellanic.</author> </bibl>).—The old <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Boeot.\">Boeot.</a></gram> </gramGrp> form was <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Ἐρχ-</orth>, and this is found in Inscrr. and on coins to the time of Alexander, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ SIG\">SIG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">60</biblScope> </bibl> <date TEIform=\"date\">(v B. C.)</date>, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ IG\">IG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">7.3166</biblScope></bibl>, al., <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">BMus.Cat.Coins Central Greece</tr_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">p.54</biblScope> </bibl>: the Arcadian Orchomenians are similarly <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang